# Frontend Configuration for Ledger Studio
# 
# ==============================================================================
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT SETUP (Backend on localhost)
# ==============================================================================
#
# OPTION 1: Using Netlify CLI (RECOMMENDED for Netlify-hosted frontend + Local backend)
# 
# Prerequisites:
#   1. Install Node.js (if not already installed)
#   2. Install Netlify CLI globally:
#      npm install -g netlify-cli
#
# Steps:
#   1. Terminal 1 - Start Backend:
#      cd backend
#      python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload
#      (Backend runs on http://localhost:8000)
#
#   2. Terminal 2 - Start Frontend with Netlify Dev:
#      cd frontend
#      netlify dev
#      (Frontend runs on http://localhost:3000)
#
#   3. Access the app:
#      Open browser to http://localhost:3000
#      Netlify CLI automatically proxies /api/* to localhost:8000
#      No CORS errors!
#
# ==============================================================================
# PRODUCTION SETUP (Backend deployed publicly)
# ==============================================================================
#
# When you deploy the backend to a public URL (e.g., https://api.yourdomain.com):
#
#   1. Update the backend URL in js/core/config.js:
#      Change: https://api.yourdomain.com/api/v1
#      OR set environment variable in Netlify dashboard
#
#   2. Ensure CORS is configured on backend for:
#      https://samsanbook.netlify.app
#
#   3. Deploy with: git push
#
# ==============================================================================

# Backend API URL (for reference - actual config is in js/core/config.js)
# Local: http://localhost:8000/api/v1
# Production: https://your-backend-domain.com/api/v1
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1

# Application name
APP_NAME=Ledger Studio (Samsan Books)